<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-10-26T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-10-26T16:00:00-05:00" n="1278" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1278">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 612.1123/5.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">American Chargé
                                    d’Affaires</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Extract.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-10-26T16:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">October 26, 1912—4 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Department’s telegram October 23, 1 p.m., your October 24, 12 noon. The
                            Department desires you to communicate to the Mexican Government the
                            position of the United States regarding the closure <pb facs="1019" n="903" xml:id="pg_903"/> of the ports as instructed in the
                            Department’s said telegram, explaining that the telegram was sent prior
                            to the receipt of news of the recapture of Vera Cruz.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Huntington Wilson.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>